TLADS Drill
 
Categorize each of the variables in the European Social Survey Data (ESS) dataset as categorical or continuous, and if continuous as ordinal, interval, or ratio variables.

Categorical: Categorical indicate a nonnumeric catagory in which data is grouped.  

    categorical - cntry, gndr, partner, year

Ordinal variables: Ordinal variables indicate rank-order.

    ordinal- happy, pplfair, pplhlp, sclmeet, sclact

Interval variables: Interval variables indicate both rank-order and distance.

    Interval- idnot, vtot

Ratio variables: Ratio variables indicate rank, distance, and a meaningful absolute zero value â€“ when a ratio variable has a score of 0, we know that none of the quantity measured by the variable is present.

    ratio- agea

